medicalBandage.description: A simple cloth wrap to dress wounds. Use it to stop bleeding damage.\nUse the secondary action to treat another player.
medicalBandage.name: Bandage

medicalFirstAidBandage.description: Bandages coated in aloe stop bleeding, heal wounds and increase abrasion healing speed.\nUse the secondary action to treat another player.
medicalFirstAidBandage.name: First Aid Bandage

medicalFirstAidKit.description: First aid kits stop bleeding, heal wounds, increase abrasion healing speed and suture lacerations.\nUse the secondary action to treat another player.
medicalFirstAidKit.name: First Aid Kit

medicalSplint.description: Heals a broken arm or leg but does not protect against further injury.\nUse the secondary action to treat another player.
medicalSplint.name: Splint

medicalPlasterCast.description: Heals a broken arm or leg more quickly than a splint but does not protect against further injury.\nUse the secondary action to treat another player.
medicalPlasterCast.name: Plaster Cast

medicalBloodBag.description: Use blood bags to craft first aid kits.
medicalBloodBag.name: Blood Bag

drugVitamins.description: These vitamins cure Fatigue and prevent you from catching ailments like Infection, Dysentery or Fatigue.
drugVitamins.name: Vitamins

drugPainkillers.description: Painkillers help you shrug off stunning blows and give you a quick boost of health. Like all chems they make you thirsty.
drugPainkillers.name: Painkillers

drugHerbalAntibiotics.description: Herbal Antibiotics can cure infections.\n\nCan be crafted in a cooking pot at a campfire.
drugHerbalAntibiotics.name: Herbal Antibiotics

drugAntibiotics.description: Antibiotics can cure infections.\n\nCan be crafted in a beaker at a campfire.
drugAntibiotics.name: Antibiotics

drugSteroids.description: Steroids decrease encumbrance, allowing you to carry more items, and allow you to run faster. They also allow you to move and perform actions normally when you have a sprained or broken limb.
drugSteroids.name: Steroids

drugFortBites.description: Fort Bites greatly increase your damage resistance.
drugFortBites.name: Fort Bites

drugAtomJunkies.description: Atom sized candy and atomic sized power! Increases the damage of explosives.
drugAtomJunkies.name: Atom Junkies

drugCovertCats.description: Be a cool cat and have it made in the shade with Covert Cats. Increases sneak attack damage.
drugCovertCats.name: Covert Cats

drugEyeKandy.description: Find that sparkling treasure easier with a drop of Eye Kandy. Increases loot quality.
drugEyeKandy.name: Eye Kandy

drugHackers.description: These tasty treats increase the amount of resources that you harvest with salvage tools.
drugHackers.name: Hackers

drugHealthBar.description: Delicious low carb bar made from all natural synthetics!\nIncreases your max health as well as your resistance to critical injuries and the speed at which they heal naturally.
drugHealthBar.name: Health Bar

drugJailBreakers.description: Be the daddy to that stubborn lock. Lockpicking is always successful.
drugJailBreakers.name: Jail Breakers

drugNerdTats.description: Channel your inner nerd powers!\nStun batons shock nearby enemies on charged hits.
drugNerdTats.name: Nerd Tats

drugOhShitzDrops.description: Be prepared for those Oh Shitz moments! Fall damage immunity.
drugOhShitzDrops.name: Oh Shitz Drops

drugRockBusters.description: Jawbreakers got nuthin' on us!\nIncrease the amount of wood, ore and stone that you harvest with mining tools.
drugRockBusters.name: Rock Busters

drugSkullCrushers.description: Rock hard candy for a rock hard punch. Increases melee damage.
drugSkullCrushers.name: Skull Crushers

drugSugarButts.description: If if's and butts were candy and nuts, every day would be Christmas! Well, now it can be with one tasty Sugar Butts Candy. Improves barter prices.
drugSugarButts.name: Sugar Butts

foodHoney.description: Honey is one of mother nature's miracles. It gives you some energy, tastes great, and can help fight off early stages of infection and pneumonia.\n(Not an instant cure)
foodHoney.name: Jar of Honey

foodCanBeef.description: It's not from your favorite steakhouse but this can of beef will fill you up. Bon appetit!
foodCanBeef.name: Large Beef Ration

foodCanChicken.description: Tastes like chicken. Well, really old synthetic chicken with dirt on it.
foodCanChicken.name: Chicken Ration

foodCanLamb.description: Lamb rations are great when the world has ended and you're on the lamb.
foodCanLamb.name: Lamb Rations

foodCanCatfood.description: A can of Meow Chow is a delicacy. For cats. You are not eating this, are you?
foodCanCatfood.name: Can of Cat Food

foodCanDogfood.description: You always wished for the life of a dog. Enjoy!
foodCanDogfood.name: Can of Dog Food

foodCanChili.description: Stash Chili goes down smooth but watch out for the fiery finish Paco.
foodCanChili.name: Can of Chili

foodCanTuna.description: A can of tuna or better known as the chicken of the wasteland.
foodCanTuna.name: Can of Tuna

foodCanSham.description:
A can of high quality Shamway Ham.
Shamway, the #1 maker of meat-like products. The lunch of champions.

Now 100% acid free!!!
foodCanSham.name: Can of Sham

foodCanSalmon.description: Enjoy this healthy can of salmon.
foodCanSalmon.name: Can of Salmon

foodCanMiso.description: It's time to soup it up with some Miso soup mmm mmm good.
foodCanMiso.name: Can of Miso

foodCanPeas.description: You and your can of peas will be like two peas in a pod and you'll get your daily vegetables.
foodCanPeas.name: Can of Peas

foodCanPears.description: Maintain that perfect pear shape by eating canned pears.
foodCanPears.name: Can of Pears

foodCanSoup.description: Chicken soup can keep the body and the soul together.
foodCanSoup.name: Chicken Soup

foodCanStock.description: Stock up on stock or you could eat it now.
foodCanStock.name: Can of Stock

foodCornOnTheCob.description: A grilled ear of corn isn't the most filling or nutritious meal but it sure is satisfying.
foodCornOnTheCob.name: Grilled Corn

foodCornBread.description: A tasty piece of corn bread lifts your spirits with its home-cooked charm.
foodCornBread.name: Corn Bread

foodShamSandwich.description: A really old sham sandwich made by Shamway. It will take away the hunger but it will also make you sick.
foodShamSandwich.name: Old Sham Sandwich

foodCharredMeat.description: Charring meat isn't the best way to cook it but it's much better than eating it raw.
foodCharredMeat.name: Charred Meat

foodGrilledMeat.description: Meat! Meat on fire! Good! Meat fresh off the grill is nutritious, delicious, and filling.
foodGrilledMeat.name: Grilled Meat

foodBoiledMeat.description: While not as yummy as grilled meat, boiling is an efficient way to prepare a meal.
foodBoiledMeat.name: Boiled Meat

foodMeatStew.description: A survivor isn't worth his salt if he can't make a meat stew.
foodMeatStew.name: Meat Stew

foodSteakAndPotato.description: A filling meal fit for a king!
foodSteakAndPotato.name: Steak and Potato Meal

foodShamChowder.description: Sham Chowder increases your Fortitude and grows chest hair!
foodShamChowder.name: Sham Chowder

foodHoboStew.description: Nutritious and deli... it's edible, okay?
foodHoboStew.name: Hobo Stew

foodFishTacos.description: Who wants to live off the land when it's taco Tuesday? Or is this Thursday?
foodFishTacos.name: Fish Tacos

foodBakedPotato.description: A nutritious baked potato full of carbohydrates. Great for couch potatoes too.
foodBakedPotato.name: Baked Potato

foodBlueberryPie.description: This homemade blueberry pie is just like Grandma used to make.
foodBlueberryPie.name: Blueberry Pie

foodPumpkinPie.description: If there is one thing to be thankful for in the apocalypse, it's pumpkin pie.
foodPumpkinPie.name: Pumpkin Pie

foodPumpkinCheesecake.description: This pumpkin cheesecake tastes delicious and grants you a 5% discount when bartering.
foodPumpkinCheesecake.name: Pumpkin Cheesecake

foodPumpkinBread.description: Pumpkin bread is more filling than corn bread and tastes amazing.
foodPumpkinBread.name: Pumpkin Bread

foodGumboStew.description: Vomiting is for the peasants! Eat like an apocalyptic king with this super filling, delicious gumbo stew.
foodGumboStew.name: Gumbo Stew

foodShepardsPie.description: Shepards Pie sure is tasty and super filling.
foodShepardsPie.name: Shepards Pie

foodSpaghetti.description: Its not a classy Italian dish, but it is very filling and has a full no money back guarantee that you won't vomit.
foodSpaghetti.name: Spaghetti

foodTunaFishGravyToast.description: Some call it shit on a shingle, but its actually pretty tasty and filling.
foodTunaFishGravyToast.name: Tuna Fish Gravy Toast

foodEggBoiled.description: A boiled egg offers up a tasty and enjoyable snack.
foodEggBoiled.name: Boiled Egg

foodBaconAndEggs.description: Bacon and eggs will really fill you up and boost your Maximum Stamina. Cholesterol is the least of your worries now.
foodBaconAndEggs.name: Bacon and Eggs

foodVegetableStew.description: Your mom always said eat your vegetables. Now's your chance to make her happy and guess what? They're good for you.
foodVegetableStew.name: Vegetable Stew

foodRawMeat.description: Meat can be eaten raw but is better charred, grilled, boiled or made into stews at a campfire.
foodRawMeat.name: Raw Meat

foodRottingFlesh.description: You would have to be pretty desperate to eat this.
foodRottingFlesh.name: Rotting Flesh

foodEgg.description: Eggs can be eaten raw but should be cooked. Used in several campfire recipes.
foodEgg.name: Egg

foodCornMeal.description: Cornmeal is used in several recipes at the campfire but you can just eat it. \nCrafted in lots of 2.
foodCornMeal.name: Cornmeal

foodCropBlueberries.description: Blueberries can be eaten, used to make pies or turned into blueberry seeds.
foodCropBlueberries.name: Blueberries

foodCropCorn.description: An ear of corn can be eaten or used to make corn seed, corn meal, grilled corn, stews and more.
foodCropCorn.name: Ear of Corn

foodCropGraceCorn.description: A mutated ear of corn that looks safe enough to eat. Probably.\nCan also be used to craft glue, Grandpa's Awesome Sauce, Grandpa's Moonshine, and Grandpa's Learnin Elixar.
foodCropGraceCorn.name: Ear of Super Corn

foodCropPotato.description: Potatoes can be eaten, crafted into seeds or used in several recipes at the campfire.
foodCropPotato.name: Potato

foodCropMushrooms.description: Mushrooms can be eaten uncooked and used in several recipes at the campfire.
foodCropMushrooms.name: Mushrooms

foodCropYuccaFruit.description: Yucca fruit is edible and can be juiced to gain a bit of water. It is harvested from cacti and yucca plants.
foodCropYuccaFruit.name: Yucca Fruit

foodCropPumpkin.description: Many don't know what to do with a pumpkin in the kitchen but it is indispensable for Helloween decorations.
foodCropPumpkin.name: Pumpkin

drinkJarRiverWater.description: Disgusting murky water but it's the apocalypse. You can't be picky. Boil at a campfire to purify it.
drinkJarRiverWater.name: Murky Water

drinkJarBoiledWater.description: Fresh bottled water. Well as fresh as you can get in the apocalypse.
drinkJarBoiledWater.name: Water

drinkJarPureMineralWater.description: Pure mineral water is good for your digestion and hydrates you for days!\nExertion will not make you hungry and thirsty as quickly.
drinkJarPureMineralWater.name: Pure Mineral Water

drinkJarGoldenRodTea.description: Greatly speeds up recovering from dysentery.
drinkJarGoldenRodTea.name: Goldenrod Tea

drinkJarRedTea.description: An ancient Chinese secret, red tea is known for being an antioxidant, providing excellent rehydration and reducing food drain so that exertion does not make you hungry and thirsty as quickly.
drinkJarRedTea.name: Red Tea

drinkYuccaJuiceSmoothie.description: This smoothie helps you survive in severely cold environments.
drinkYuccaJuiceSmoothie.name: Yucca Juice Smoothie

drinkCanMegaCrush.description: Crush your enemies and your thirst with Mega Crush! It's got electrolytes!
drinkCanMegaCrush.name: Mega Crush

drinkJarCoffee.description: Coffee keeps your stamina up and helps you stay warm for a limited time.
drinkJarCoffee.name: Coffee

drinkJarBlackStrapCoffee.description: Blackstrap Coffee. This 2 century old favorite coffee was a staple among miners in the 1800's. Otherwise known as 'Muckmen Blackstrap' this strong blended roast will give you long lasting energy and keep you warm for hours.
drinkJarBlackStrapCoffee.name: Blackstrap Coffee

drinkJarBeer.description:
300% Fist Melee Damage
50% Stamina Gain

Gain stamina, bravado and stun immunity all in one bottle of this tasty home brewed beer. Just like grandpa used to make.
drinkJarBeer.name: Beer

drinkJarGrandpasMoonshine.description: Nuthin' makes settling it the old way easier than a bottle of grandpa's moonshine.\nGives all melee damage a punch that will make 'em quake in their boots.
drinkJarGrandpasMoonshine.name: Grandpa's Moonshine

drinkJarGrandpasAwesomeSauce.description: Tired of getting bent by those pesky traders?\nTake a shot of Grandpa's Awesome Sauce\nand get a better deal!
drinkJarGrandpasAwesomeSauce.name: Grandpa's Awesome Sauce

drinkJarGrandpasLearningElixir.description: Learn twice as much, twice as fast, or sumthin like that.
drinkJarGrandpasLearningElixir.name: Grandpas Learnin' Elixir

drinkJarGrandpasForgettingElixir.description: So potent that you probably won't remember who you are.\n(It resets your skill points, okay?)
drinkJarGrandpasForgettingElixir.name: Grandpa's Fergit'n Elixir

bucketEmpty.description: An empty bucket can be used to fill up and transport water.
bucketEmpty.name: Bucket

bucketRiverWater.description: Water can be dumped into an enclosed structure or hole in the ground to store it.
bucketRiverWater.name: Bucket of Water

noteDuke01.description: Just a friendly reminder that you pay on time, every time or there will be consequences. Next time we won't be so nice. Thanks for the gear, but you still owe us. See you soon. -The Duke
noteDuke01.name: Note from The Duke of Navezgane

q_basicSurvival.description: A mysterious note from a stranger. I don't know how I got it.
q_basicSurvival.name: Basic Survival Quest Note

qtest_nextTraderAdmin.description: Starts a quest to point you to the nearest trader.
qtest_nextTraderAdmin.name: Dev: Find Trader Quest

resourceRockSmall.description: Used in many recipes including stone axes, campfires & arrows. Can be thrown to distract zombies & are a core forging resource.
resourceRockSmall.name: Small Stone

resourceSnowBall.description: You know what to do! Turn it into first rate Yucca Juice Smoothie of course.\nCan be thrown to distract zombies.
resourceSnowBall.name: Snowball

resourceAcid.description: A resource used in crafting recipes.
resourceAcid.name: Bottle of Acid

resourceYuccaFibers.description: Plant fibers are acquired from destroying grass & small plants. Can be used to craft many things.
resourceYuccaFibers.name: Plant Fibers

resourceWood.description: A piece of wood. Great for building tools and constructing wood frames for building.
resourceWood.name: Wood

resourceCrushedSand.description: Crushed sand is a core resource that can be smelted in the forge to make glass and used to craft items.
resourceCrushedSand.name: Crushed Sand

resourceBrokenGlass.description: Broken glass can be smelted into glass (sand) at the forge or used to end it all if the apocalypse is just too much for you.
resourceBrokenGlass.name: Broken Glass

resourceScrapIron.description: A core resource for crafting, forging, and repairing. Next to wood there's nothing more useful.
resourceScrapIron.name: Iron

resourceForgedIron.description: Can be crafted at the forge and be used to craft, repair and upgrade a variety of things.
resourceForgedIron.name: Forged Iron

resourceMetalPipe.description: A rather ordinary short iron pipe. Can be used in a variety of recipes.
resourceMetalPipe.name: Short Iron Pipe

resourceForgedSteel.description: Can be crafted at the forge after installing a crucible upgrade. Steel is used to make some of the strongest items.
resourceForgedSteel.name: Forged Steel

resourceScrapPolymers.description: Bits of rubber and plastics that you may carefully mold into new shapes.
resourceScrapPolymers.name: Scrap Polymers

resourceSewingKit.description: Use to craft clothing, armor, and make modifications to them. Can also be used to treat bleeding and lacerations.\nUse the secondary action to treat another player.
resourceSewingKit.name: Sewing Kit

resourceOilShale.description: Oil shale can be found in the desert and crafted into gas at a chemistry station.
resourceOilShale.name: Oil Shale

resourceBone.description: An ordinary bone from an animal. Probably.
resourceBone.name: Bone

resourceLeather.description: Leather can be used to make a variety of things including clothing, crossbows and bellows for a forge.
resourceLeather.name: Leather

resourceAnimalFat.description: Animal fat can be eaten raw or used in cooking or other crafting recipes.
resourceAnimalFat.name: Animal Fat

resourceTestosteroneExtract.description: A compound used to create steroids that is harvested from bears.
resourceTestosteroneExtract.name: Testosterone Extract

resourceCropHopsFlower.description: The hops flower is a critical ingredient for brewing beer.
resourceCropHopsFlower.name: Hops Flower

resourceCropAloeLeaf.description: Can be used to craft items with healing properties.
resourceCropAloeLeaf.name: Aloe Vera Leaf

resourceCropChrysanthemumPlant.description: Used to brew tea and craft other items.
resourceCropChrysanthemumPlant.name: Chrysanthemum

resourceCropCottonPlant.description: Used to craft cloth and other items.
resourceCropCottonPlant.name: Cotton

resourceCropCoffeeBeans.description: Brew coffee at a campfire or craft the beans into coffee seeds.
resourceCropCoffeeBeans.name: Coffee Beans

resourceScrapBrass.description: A core resource for forging that can be used to make ammo casings in the forge.
resourceScrapBrass.name: Brass

resourceScrapLead.description: A core resource for forging can be used to make bullet tips and more in the forge.
resourceScrapLead.name: Lead

resourceClayLump.description: Clay Soil or Loam is a key resource for forging and farming and can be harvested from the top soil of nearly every biome.
resourceClayLump.name: Clay Soil

resourceCobblestones.description: Cobblestone rocks can be used to build surprisingly sturdy cobblestone structures.
resourceCobblestones.name: Cobblestone Rocks

resourceCement.description: Cement is used to craft concrete mix. This requires a cement mixer.
resourceCement.name: Cement

resourceConcreteMix.description: Can be used as a resource to upgrade cobblestone into solid concrete walls or to craft concrete blocks in a cement mixer.
resourceConcreteMix.name: Concrete Mix

resourceCloth.description: Cloth is a staple for survival used for clothing, bandages and more.
resourceCloth.name: Cloth Fragment

resourcePaper.description: Paper can be used with other ingredients to make shotgun ammo, dynamite, and cigars. Crafted in lots of 10.
resourcePaper.name: Paper

resourceMilitaryFiber.description: Military grade synthetic fibers are used to craft military clothing and armor. \nCraft in lots of 10.
resourceMilitaryFiber.name: Military Fiber

resourceHeadlight.description: A headlight is useful for creating a vehicle and lighting.
resourceHeadlight.name: Headlight

resourceMechanicalParts.description: Small parts like sprockets, nuts and bolts.
resourceMechanicalParts.name: Mechanical Parts

resourceSpring.description: Springs are great for making furniture, steel doors, hatches and more.
resourceSpring.name: Spring

resourceGlue.description: Glue is useful for making your own duct tape.
resourceGlue.name: Glue

resourceDuctTape.description: Duct tape is useful for making many things & according to Madmole MacDyver a must have resource for making the cooler stuff.
resourceDuctTape.name: Duct Tape

resourceFeather.description: Feathers are primarily found in bird nests or by harvesting birds. They can be used to craft arrows and crossbow bolts.
resourceFeather.name: Feather

resourceArrowHeadIron.description: An iron broadhead tip used to craft iron arrows and bolts.
resourceArrowHeadIron.name: Iron Arrowhead

resourceArrowHeadSteelAP.description: A bodkin arrowhead made from steel. Used to craft armor-piercing arrows and bolts.
resourceArrowHeadSteelAP.name: Steel Arrowhead

resourceCoal.description: A great fuel source and a core ingredient for gunpowder.
resourceCoal.name: Coal

resourcePotassiumNitratePowder.description: Hey captain caveman! Nitrate has many uses in crafting such as making gunpowder. Cave stalagmites are rich in it.
resourcePotassiumNitratePowder.name: Nitrate Powder

resourceGunPowder.description: Gunpowder made from coal and nitrate can be used to make your own ammo and explosives.
resourceGunPowder.name: Gunpowder

resourceBuckshot.description: Buckshot used to make shotgun ammo. Can be crafted at a forge with clay and lead.
resourceBuckshot.name: Buckshot

resourceBulletCasing.description: Bullet casings can be crafted at the forge and are used to craft firearm ammunition.
resourceBulletCasing.name: Bullet Casing

resourceBulletTip.description: Bullet tips can be crafted at the forge and are used to craft firearm ammunition.
resourceBulletTip.name: Bullet Tip

resourceNail.description: Nails are used to build furniture, large storage crates and as ammo for the nail gun.
resourceNail.name: Nails

resourceRocketTip.description: A rocket tip is used to make ammo for the rocket launcher.
resourceRocketTip.name: Rocket Tip

resourceRocketCasing.description: A rocket casing is used to make ammo for the rocket launcher.
resourceRocketCasing.name: Rocket Casing

resourceWaterFilter.description: A component used in the crafting of a Dew Collector.
resourceWaterFilter.name: Water Filter

resourceRepairKit.description: Repair Kits are used to repair held and worn items, vehicles, and more.
resourceRepairKit.name: Repair Kit

resourceOil.description: Oil is a key ingredient for crafting traps and various mods.
resourceOil.name: Oil

resourcePaint.description: Use a paint brush to paint building blocks. Crafted in lots of 250 in the Campfire, and 500 in the Chemistry Station.
resourcePaint.name: Paint

candle.description: A candle can be carried as a light source or placed on walls. This might attract zombies.
candle.name: Candle

smallEngine.description: A common part for a vehicles or generators.
smallEngine.name: Engine

carBattery.description: Car batteries can be used to craft vehicles as well as scrapped or smelted at the forge for lead. Recharge them in a powered battery bank.
carBattery.name: Lead Car Battery

casinoCoin.description: A Duke's casino coin. After the epidemic and war these brass coins became the main currency for trading in Navezgane.\n\nCan be smelted in a forge to craft firearm ammunition.
casinoCoin.name: Duke's Casino Token

oldCash.description: This used to be legal tender. Now it is mostly valued for being made of paper.
oldCash.name: Old Cash

solarCell.description: Place solar cells into a solar cell bank to generate power.
solarCell.name: Solar Cell

toolCookingGrill.description: A cooking utensil used in the campfire to unlock recipes.
toolCookingGrill.name: Cooking Grill

toolCookingPot.description: A cooking utensil used in the campfire to unlock recipes.
toolCookingPot.name: Cooking Pot

toolBeaker.description: A cooking utensil used in the campfire to unlock recipes.
toolBeaker.name: Beaker

toolBellows.description: A tool that can be installed in a forge. It increases air flow and so the smelting speed of the forge.
toolBellows.name: Advanced Bellows

toolAnvil.description: A tool that can be installed in a forge. It increases the crafting speed of that forge.
toolAnvil.name: Anvil

toolForgeCrucible.description: A crucible upgrade is required to craft forged steel, steel arrowheads, and bulletproof glass in a forge.
toolForgeCrucible.name: Crucible

resourceLockPick.description: If you have lockpicks in your inventory then you can pick some locks by holding 'E' and selecting the Pick Lock action.\nThey do not need to be equipped on the hotbar.
resourceLockPick.name: Lockpick

resourceLockPickBundle.description: This is a compact stack of lockpicks. Use this item to open and unpack it.
resourceLockPickBundle.name: Stack of Lockpicks (50)

harvestingToolsSkillMagazine.description: Learn to craft your own tools from the best in the industry!\n\nImproves harvesting tool crafting skill.
harvestingToolsSkillMagazine.name: Tools Digest

repairToolsSkillMagazine.description: From the home repair enthusiast to the professional repairman, we’ve got you covered!\n\nImproves repair tool crafting skill.
repairToolsSkillMagazine.name: Handy Land

salvageToolsSkillMagazine.description: One man’s junk is another man’s treasure!\n\nImproves salvage tool crafting skill.
salvageToolsSkillMagazine.name: Scrapping 4 Fun

knucklesSkillMagazine.description: Tired of being bullied? Give your rivals a fat lip with a knuckle sandwich!\n\nImproves knuckles crafting skill.
knucklesSkillMagazine.name: Furious Fists

bladesSkillMagazine.description: Be a real knife guy! Get the best info on all your bladed weapon needs.\n\nImproves blade crafting skill.
bladesSkillMagazine.name: Knife Guy

clubsSkillMagazine.description: Check out all the latest clubs and bats for sports, home defense, and gang wars!\n\nImproves club crafting skill.
clubsSkillMagazine.name: Big Hitters

sledgehammersSkillMagazine.description: If you like smashing stuff, Get Hammered has you covered!\n\nImproves sledgehammer crafting skill.
sledgehammersSkillMagazine.name: Get Hammered

spearsSkillMagazine.description: If you like poking holes in things, Sharp Sticks has you covered!\n\nImproves spear crafting skill.
spearsSkillMagazine.name: Sharp Sticks

bowsSkillMagazine.description: Who has time to stand in line at the hunting store? Make your own bows and save your money for the next issue of Bow Hunter’s Magazine!\n\nImproves bow crafting skill.
bowsSkillMagazine.name: Bow Hunters

handgunsSkillMagazine.description: Do you feel lucky? Well, luck is for losers! Be prepared and learn how to craft your own handguns.\n\nImproves handgun crafting skill.
handgunsSkillMagazine.name: Handgun Magazine

shotgunsSkillMagazine.description: Whether it’s single shot, double barrel, pump, or auto shotguns, we have you covered!\n\nImproves shotgun crafting skill.
shotgunsSkillMagazine.name: Shotgun Weekly

riflesSkillMagazine.description: Check out vintage and modern hunting rifles in this amazing issue of Rifle World.\n\nImproves rifle crafting skill.
riflesSkillMagazine.name: Rifle World

machineGunsSkillMagazine.description: Check out the latest assault rifles on the market and even learn how to build your own from common household items!\n\nImproves assault rifle crafting skill.
machineGunsSkillMagazine.name: Tactical Warfare

explosivesSkillMagazine.description: Blowing stuff up is our business, and business is good! If it goes boom, we cover it in this explosive issue!\n\nImproves explosives crafting skill.
explosivesSkillMagazine.name: Explosive Magazine

roboticsSkillMagazine.description: Learn to create do-it-yourself electronics from everyday junk and be the envy of your peers!\n\nImproves robotics crafting skill.
roboticsSkillMagazine.name: Tech Planet

armorSkillMagazine.description: Check out all the latest armor designs for the modern warrior!\n\nImproves armor crafting skill.
armorSkillMagazine.name: Armored Up

medicalSkillMagazine.description: Learn life saving skills! Make bandages and medical supplies from common household items.\n\nImproves medical crafting skill.
medicalSkillMagazine.name: Medical Journal

foodSkillMagazine.description: Learn to cook dozens of amazing meals and become a Master Chef!\n\nImproves food crafting skill.
foodSkillMagazine.name: Home Cooking Weekly
